# TypeScript SOP

- Prefer strict mode (`strict`, `noUncheckedIndexedAccess` when project enables it).
- Avoid `any`; use `unknown` + narrowing at boundaries; document bounded `any` if unavoidable.
- Explicit return types on public APIs and exported functions.
- Prefer discriminated unions and type guards over loose string unions.
- Utility types (`Pick`, `Omit`, `Partial`) for API evolution; avoid deep nested generics without aliases.
- Prefer `async/await`; handle errors at boundaries; no floating promises in app code.
- No secrets in source; validate env at startup with schema (zod/valibot) when the repo uses it.
- Match eslint/prettier; run `type-check` / `lint` before marking tasks done.
- Tests: colocate `*.test.ts` / `__tests__`; mock at I/O boundaries, not internals.
- Imports: prefer type-only imports; avoid barrel files that hurt tree-shaking unless repo convention.
